window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>#1 Bestseller in Organized Crime!</p> <p>Maria</p> <p>The first time I met my fiancé, I put him in a chokehold.</p> <p>I wanted nothing to do with the man whose family tore my life to pieces.</p> <p>Matteo De Luca was vicious claws sheathed in refinement and class.</p> <p>He saw my untamed independence as a challenge.</p> <p>I saw his alluring authority as a threat.</p> <p>The worst part? I wanted to experience whatever it was Matteo had to offer, and I hated myself for it.</p> <p>I wanted to launch myself at him.</p> <p>To kiss him. To kill him.</p> <p>To end the debilitating torture of the unknown.</p> <p>The moment our paths collided, our lives were altered irrevocably.</p> <p>Taking us from enemies allied by a strategic marriage to something dark and consuming.</p> <p>Something that tasted like obsession.</p> <p>What to know about Blood Always:</p> <p>-Mafia arranged marriage</p> <p>-Enemies to lovers</p> <p>-Badass FMC</p> <p>-Who hurt you?</p> <p>-Jealous/possessive MMC</p> <p>-Unexpected pregnancy</p> <p>-Has an HEA</p> <p>-Can be read as a standalone</p> <p>-Dual POV</p> <p>-Content warnings listed on my website</p> <p>A Note from the Author: For those of you who are new to me, I write what I'd call \"mafia lite.\" My heroes are hardened criminals with soft spots for their heroines. There may be violence and cruelty in my books, but never between the main characters. Enjoy!</p>"; 
